HEADWORD: Curer
<hw>Cur"er</hw> <pr>(-?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
cures; a healer; a physician.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who prepares beef, fish, etc., for preservation
by drying, salting, smoking, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>curettage</ent>⟦br⟧
